description: yeah but a lot of digital nomad are in situations like myself who dont actually have a home period. i dont have family to go back to, and i havent lived in my birthed country for years so i wouldnt even know where the heck to go, im in a situation where japan kicking me out regardless that there are no flights that are not like 42hr long and most country will mandatory quarantine you and test or need covid insurance, so now im completely fucked and dying for countrys to start opening up for tourism for my wellbeing. thank the world for immigration in a time like this, its BS.

author: David Carnes
description: I am overseas now. If I try to return home I gotta go through at least 6 airports, plus about 18 hours on a plane sitting next to other people. Plus I maintain no residence back home; I\'d have to live with my 78-year old mother who has diabetes. If I got it and gave it to her she\'d probably die. So I\'m staying put for now. But what if my visa expires?

author: Sophia Cook
description: I completely agree that traveling right now spreads the virus. But I\'d like to point out that 1) not all digital nomads are younger than 40 (I\'m not) and 2) not everyone has a place to go back to. Like another commenter says, what do you suggest? Traveling there from current location seems unhelpful to anyone. I am hunkering down in the UK and thankfully have a place to stay.
